                        "I get up early every day.",
                        "So now we’re getting worried about money."
                      ],
                      "columnB": [
                        "We use the present progressive with dynamic verbs to describe actions in a picture, video, etc.",
                        "Stative verbs (want, seem) frequently describe feelings and ideas. We use the simple present with stative verbs.",
                        "We use the present progressive with dynamic verbs to talk about actions that are in progress at the moment of speaking or writing. ",
                        "A few verbs (have, look, speak, think) have two or more meanings. They are sometimes dynamic verbs and sometimes stative verbs.",
                        "We use the simple present with dynamic verbs to talk about actions that always, usually or never happen.",
                        "We use the present progressive with dynamic verbs to describe trends (e.g. something is happening more and more these days). "
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
